title: World on a String
lyrics:
You know I lose,
you know I win
You know I call for
the shape I'm in.
It's just a game you
see me play,

Only real in the way

That I feel

from day to day.



Although the answer

is not unknown,

I'm searchin', searchin',

and how I've grown.

It's not all right

to say goodbye,

And the world on a string

Doesn't mean a thing.



No, the world on a string

Doesn't mean a thing.

It's only real in the way

That I feel from day to day.

No, the world on a string

Doesn't mean a thing.
